review_blob:
Dark black with opaque espresso hints tan thin head with stable lace. Malts up front on the nose with a hint of whiskey barrel in the background. Hints of vanilla and sweet cinnamon on the nose. Great foamy mouthfeel with vanilla ice cream and light roast coffee. Vanilla finish gives a dessert like feel without any overbearing sweetness. 

---That dog will hunt!
beer_name: Rahr & Sons Bourbon Barrel Aged Winter Warmer

review_blob:
Amber malts hit the nose paired with some Citrus hops. Mouthfeel is adequate but the balance is great. Malts are loud but the hops keep up. Finish goes on a hoppy journey from earthy to citrus with a finish of grassy/piney. Really fun!!

---That dog will hunt!

Malt syrup on the nose a touch of agave nectar. Palate is simple but adequate. A bit too sweet. Brown sugar syrup and oak vanillin. Not very balanced. 

---That dog will hunt!

Nose is almost off. Hints of dust and peat smoke with some malty complexity. Palate is nice, structured and refined. Very contemplative taste. Wild tobacco and peat smoke. Touch of syrupy gamey earth. Hops are not loud at all. Would drink again. 

---That dog will hunt!

Nose is malt dominant with hints of yeastyness buried deeper is some darker earthy hops. Palate is adequate. Malts dominate the flavor without causing a syrup or sugary note. Mid palate the hops jump up to say hello but are quickly washed away by some subtle dried fruits. 

---That dog will hunt!

Lighter gold with no head. Heavy on candy. Like orange and flowers dipped in toffee. Follows on palate with clean finish. Well hidden alc. nice offering! 

---That dog will hunt!

Standard golden hay color with thin lasting lace. Nose of sweet grass, touch of caramel, and bitter orange oil. Candied herbs and burnt grass? Unique. Not my favorite but worth a try. 

---That dog will hunt!

Dark copper. Stable pale lace. Oranges and baking spices on the nose. Malty palate with rich mouthfeel. Leaves pleasant earthy bitter finish. 

---That dog will hunt!
beer_name: Uinta Detour Double India Pale Ale

review_blob:
Light amber very cloudy. Nose slightly more mute than expected. Hint of grass and spice. Thick mouthfeel, very rich. Malts are big, grassy toffee. Hops are rich and lingering.

---That dog will hunt!

Light amber slightly cloudy. Interesting Sauvignon blanc and lime note with a touch of grass on the nose. Rich mouthfeel confirming wine flavor on the nose. Malts quite well balanced with a hint of toffee, hops actually rather mellow adding some spice and some earthy finish that lingers a bit. Good but not a hop bomb. 

---That dog will hunt!

Cloudy thin foamy head with fine lace. Neutral nose with hint of grass and citrus pits (if that existed). Thick mouthfeel. Wow what a trip of flavors. Starts bright with malty graininess quickly followed by an interesting coffee note? Super earthy finish with a loamy bitterness that lingers. Wow super complexity. 

---That dog will hunt!

Dark straw hay color. Stable whitish foam head light fresh earthy hoppy nose with citrus and beachy nose. Great thick mouthfeel. Clean finish with very little ibu. 


---That dog will hunt!

The color of dr pepper. No head at all. Espresso and molasses. Mouthfeel has a delicate creaminess. Malts are surprisingly light if it wasn't for the espresso notes and the color I never would have guessed the black part. Finish is clean but a bit short. 

---That dog will hunt!

Dark dark dark with a stable creamy foam head.  Nose is burnt caramel with some vanilla undertones. Mouthfeel is ok. A little thin but it is late in the beer drinking evening. Malty sweetness dominated but is cleaned away by a piney hop presence that finishes with a hint of spice. 

---That dog will hunt!

Dark amber with no head. Nose is mostly an earthy grainy with a slight bright grass and lemon. Mouth is a bit syrupy but with good creaminess. Taste is amazing. What a progression of flavors! It starts sweet with a candied apricot switching to a rich full east coast style ipa. But the finish!! Cleans up the malts and the hops sing loud!! Big grassy earthy hops. Nice surprise. I've never had anything from them. Great first impression. 

---That dog will hunt!

Pours dark dark brown. Nose is super! Thick burnt sugars soaked in bourbon and a candied fruit. Mouthfeel is thick and slightly syrupy. Wow huge thick malts up front with a boozy syrup finishing with something that reminds me of ice cream. Maybe the vanilla. Quite a beast. 

---That dog will hunt!

Pours dark gold with a quickly dissipating head. Bright mandarin and lemon nose. Mouthfeel is thick without being syrupy. Malts stand up and compete with the earthy hops at first but then the bright piney notes take over and leave a pleasant fresh hoppy finish. 

---That dog will hunt!

Kind if a weird nose. Kind of skunky. Not sure if I like it. Mouthfeel is quite sharp but nice. Huge green blast. I don't know the ibu but must be close to 100. Took half the bottle for my palate to adjust and then the complex notes started to come out. Some gamey stone fruits and old dried grass. Interesting, the torpedo crowd would love it but it is very grassy green. 

---That dog will hunt!

Heavy skunky nose with a richness that I want to attribute to malts. Thick without being syrupy. Great mouthfeel. Malts definetly speak louder but hops are there. Big on mid palate and finish. Quite well balenced I wish the aroma was a touch more hoppy. 

---That dog will hunt!

Fruity soda like nose? Root beer? Slightly coying mid palate. 4th beer of the night. Not very exciting. 

---That dog will hunt!

In bottle. Dark amber malty nose with a slight sweetness. Hops are hidden under the sweetness with a touch of stone fruit. Mouthfeel is slightly thick with modest carbonation. Nutty malty taste with sweetness hitting at the same time as the hops finish is clean with decent length. Worth the drink but not memorable. 

---That dog will hunt!

Unfiltered dark honey amber color. Wonderfully pillowy white foam very stable and lacy head. Citrusy hops and floral yeast dominate the nose. Wow great mouthfeel. The fruit jumps out first on the palate. Some apricot stone fruits, creamy crystal malts follow mid palate with finally the hops standing up at the end. Slight bitterness with a clean lingering fresh grass. 

---That dog will hunt!
beer_name: Boulevard Smokestack Series - Tank 7 Farmhouse Ale

review_blob:
Light color. Wow really cool nose with kiwi banana and tropical fruit. Slight Belgium yeastyness. Great mouthfeel. Mentholy and sweet with an interesting banana cream finish. Fun and interesting but not something I could drink a ton of. 

---That dog will hunt!

Good looking! Nice light amber color with stable white head. Nose is citrusy and complex with a lingering fruit note. Nice mouthfeel. Clean malts quickly overrun by A clean noble hop bitterness, little bigger hop profile than expected but still awesome. Hint of malt pops up on the end too. 

---That dog will hunt!

Nose is great floral herbs. Rosemary and basil. Fantastic nose. Taster bottle so no carb. Great mid palate with malts singing through shortly until the hops punch back up to finish out. Great stuff. 

---That dog will hunt!

Dark caramel color. Nose I medicinal and grassy very scotch like malts sing. Palate is creamy. Great mouthful of peaty salt with hops hiding up mid palate. Finish is bigger bitters than I would expect from a scotch. Good stuff. 

---That dog will hunt!

Great darker gold color with a stable dark cream head. Nose is gorgeous round citrus with piny sappy overtones. Great mouthfeel. Wow fantastic. This is right down my alley. Bitterness is super complex with rosemary and citrus rind hints. Finish is long and luscious. Great beer. 

---That dog will hunt!

Light barely golden color with a pine and lime rind nose very refreshing and bright. Mouthfeel is as expected. Can't find malts anywhere. Finish is grassy with a clean bitterness that lingers for quite some time. Well put together but kind of simple on the palate. 

---That dog will hunt!

Dark gold. Nose is small with a hint of stone fruit and grass. Great mouthfeel. Finish is singing to me. The hops are crisp and well defined. Clean grass and underripe peaches. Very nice. 

---That dog will hunt!

review_blob:
Pale gold with a neutral nose not tellin me much maybe some stone fruit and grass. Belgium yeast is a nice addition but leaves a bit of a metallic linger. Mouthfeel is a bit thin. Pretty good.

Dark gold with a clean slightly fruit inspired nose peaches and blossoms. Mouthfeel is great. Stone fruit and clean hop finish. So drinkable.

beer_name: Ommegang Scythe and Sickle Harvest Ale

review_blob:
Dark honeys amber color with a sappy apricot nose rich with hints of honey. Mouthfeel is ok not as creamy as it could be. Bitterness is a bit overwhelming midpalate. Cover up some of the delicate flavors. Finish is like a double ipa with some sappy resinous long taste. 

---That dog will hunt!
beer_name: Hops & Grain French Oak Aged Pale Dog

review_blob:
Pours dark with a creamy pale brown head. Nose is great. Spicy gingerbread with nutmeg and cinnamon, coffee malts hide in the background. Great mouthfeel. Spices are very tight in mid palate. Stout in the front and stout on the finish with ginger and spice in the middle. Finish is lingering dark malt with a touch of hop presence just to clean up. 

---That dog will hunt!

Pours a dark golden pale with a very fine lace. Nose is eggy and banana like with a touch of nutmeg clovy spice. Nails the carbonation. Adds a creamy element. Flavor is quite complex. Bread and ginger with a subtle hint of cinnamon spice. Hops are just barely finishing out. Not bad at all. 

---That dog will hunt!

I believe this is the centennial hop version but I any find any markings. Nose is grassy with a touch of toasted grapefruit. Palate is great just the right amount of carbonation. Flavor is surprisingly juicy with a sappy intensity. Very fun to drink as the hops really sing a clear note.  Worth a try

---That dog will hunt!
beer_name: Two Brothers Heavy Handed India Pale Ale

review_blob:
Mmm candied citrus orange nose! Quite pretty. Great mouthfeel! Hops are complex and well layered. Strong citrus mid palate and a floral bitter finish that lingers a clean finish. A surprise. 

---That dog will hunt!

Smells like sweet autumn. Light nutmeg and melon on the nose. Thick and viscous, carbonation could be better integrated. Finish has a gentle baking spice complexity. Kinda fun to drink. 

---That dog will hunt!

Great nose. Malts with a grassy grapefruit background very reminiscent of 90 min. Very clean precise hops. Malts fall back on the taste Nd rally allow the well balanced citrus and grass intensity to finish with a clean long bitter finish that make me want more. A nice surprise.  

---That dog will hunt!

Mute nose. Maybe a hint of malt. Nice caramel palate with a bitter overlay that is quite nice. Lingering hop profile is pleasant with a decidedly citrus note. Darker than I would expect. But not bad.

beer_name: Goose Island Green Line Pale Ale

review_blob:
Mute nose with a hint of wheaty yeast. Mouth is brighter than I thought. Hop profile is nice. Citrus only though. Finish is clean pilsner like. Ok not the best but fun. 

---That dog will hunt!

Clean nose with slight grassiness and hint of sweet malt on nose.  Mouthfeel is a little abrasive up front with a surprisingly creamy finish. The finish reminds me of a white whiskey. A small sharp punch of alcohol, not quite boozy but a clean almost vodka like minerality. Malts don't stand up as much as I would expect for the style. Kinda like a Belgium pale ale. Finish is confusing in a good way. Pretty good.

review_blob:
Pop cloves and woody banana with a nutmeg earthiness. Creamy mouthfeel with surprisingly conditioned like carbonation. Malts are present but yeast wins this battle. Finish is complex and changing. Unique beer worth trying.

Clean malt nose with a touch of yeasty spice. Good mouthfeel with a creamy carbonation. Very clean almost banana like flavor. Almost no bitterness. Clean malt on finish with almost no lingering flavor.

Huge dark malt hit with espresso punch mid palate. The finish is rich and chocolatey. Would be a bit more complex with warmth. I have to let this one warm up. Worth it's rating.

Citrus nose with slight malt backbone. Nice head. Alc is noticeable but pleasant. Great structure here. Very enjoyable. Can't talk gotta drink.

Super aroma. Floral with citrus rind notes. Nice mouthfeel. Hops are pronounced and surprisingly flavorful grass and citrus rind with a chalky clean bitter hopped finish. Very surprising for a local.
